                                "game-obj": "Traits",
                                "game-id": "60a4f011afd1e0fac8211bd01108d104",
                                "text": "This magic comes from the primal tradition, connecting to the natural world and instinct. Anything with this trait is magical.  \n  \nA creature with this trait is primarily constituted of or has a strong connection to primal magic."
                            }
                        ],
                        "frequency": "three times per day",
                        "effect": "The leprechaun produces an item out of their hat, from behind their jacket, from within a hole in a tree stump, or from any other unexpected location. This conjured item must be no more than 1 Bulk and must be made of relatively commonplace material (such as cloth, wood, stone, or even low-value metal like iron or lead). It can't rely on intricate artistry or complex moving parts, never fulfills a Cost or the like, and can't be made of precious materials or materials with a rarity of uncommon or higher. The created object is temporary and lasts for 1 hour or until the leprechaun creates a new item, whichever comes first."
                    }
                },
                {
                    "name": "Leprechaun Magic",
                    "type": "stat_block_section",
                    "subtype": "offensive_action",
                    "offensive_action_type": "ability",
                    "ability": {
                        "type": "stat_block_section",
                        "subtype": "ability",
                        "ability_type": "offensive",
                        "name": "Leprechaun Magic",
                        "links": [
                            {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "te spells",
                                "alt": "te spells",
                                "game-obj": "Rules",
                                "aonid": 2901
                            }
                        ],
                        "text": "Leprechauns love to use their magic to beguile others, and after generations of doing so, they've developed a strong connection to such tricks. When a leprechaun uses their innate spells to deceive, trick, or humiliate a creature, the spell DC increases to 20 and the attack modifier to +12."
                    }
                }
            ]
